   <title>CobbAPI Documentation Index</title>
   <description>
      <p>
         CobbAPI is a resource provided for mod authors: an SKSE-powered DLL that adds numerous 
         native functions to the Papyrus script engine. CobbAPI does not extend existing Papyrus 
         classes (due to compatibility risks); rather, it adds secondary Papyrus classes with 
         global functions, which receive the subject of any given action as an argument. For 
         example:
      </p>
      <pre>Bool bIsHorse = CobbAPIActor.IsHorse(kMyActor)</pre>
   </description>
   <abstract-types>
      <type name="actor-value-index">
         The numeric index of an actor value.
      </type>
      <type name="bounds">
         An array of six floats representing an oriented bounding box, in the form of 
         two coordinate triplets: a "min" point and a "max" point.
      </type>
   </abstract-types>
